Another gotcha with for loops: scoping is a little weird.<p><pre><code>    	xs := []int{1,2,3}
	for _, x := range xs {
		go func() {
			fmt.Println(x)
		}()
	}
</code></pre>
That prints `3 3 3` not `1 2 3`. You can fix it like this:<p><pre><code>        for i := range xs {
		x := xs[i]
		go func() {
			fmt.Println(x)
		}()
	}
</code></pre>
Which seems like it ought to be the default behavior.
